194
00:11:13,559 --> 00:11:17,929
So organizations with centralized
governance contain breaches in minutes,

195
00:11:18,239 --> 00:11:21,029
fragment one measure it in days.

196
00:11:21,609 --> 00:11:24,849
That gap is your lateral exposure window

197
00:11:25,349 --> 00:11:30,369
So let's talk about infrastructure
level impacts the three pillars, right?

198
00:11:30,769 --> 00:11:35,629
Everything I have described here produces
three infrastructure level outcomes.

199
00:11:36,379 --> 00:11:37,959
Reduced attack in surface.

200
00:11:38,099 --> 00:11:42,859
So least privilege limits what a
compromised identity can reach.

201
00:11:43,439 --> 00:11:47,749
So limited lateral movement and
then continuous verification

202
00:11:47,759 --> 00:11:51,729
stops stolen credentials from
traversing the pipeline undetected.

203
00:11:52,599 --> 00:11:54,429
Fastest incident recovery.

204
00:11:54,429 --> 00:11:57,549
So centralized governance
enables system-wide revocation

205
00:11:57,709 --> 00:11:58,739
and pre-built playbooks.

206
00:11:58,749 --> 00:12:04,089
So unless you have that, you cannot
recover from a incident faster.

207
00:12:04,589 --> 00:12:10,779
So pretty much it's if it is like less
reach, less movement faster recovery.

208
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:13,999
That's the whole thesis
in the three words each.

209
00:12:14,499 --> 00:12:17,439
So let's discuss the
architecture principles.

210
00:12:18,119 --> 00:12:19,529
Identity by design.

211
00:12:20,389 --> 00:12:25,319
So define boundaries, trust relationships,
and scopes before you build the pipeline,

212
00:12:25,779 --> 00:12:27,729
not after the production failure, right?

213
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:30,969
Not after onboarding your
pipeline into production.

214
00:12:31,799 --> 00:12:33,099
Zero implicit trust.

215
00:12:33,099 --> 00:12:37,969
So every component authenticates and
authorizes independently regardless

216
00:12:37,969 --> 00:12:40,289
